HEADWORD: Antipeptone
<hw>An`ti*pep"tone</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n`t⟦icr⟧*p⟦ecr⟧p"t⟦omac⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A product of gastric and
pancreatic digestion, differing from hemipeptone in not being decomposed
by the continued action of pancreatic juice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antiperiodic</ent>⟦br⟧
